  "description": "This dataset comprises behavioral and EEG neuroimaging data from a reinforcement learning task administered to 50 healthy control participants following either sad or neutral mood manipulations (25 per condition). The task included training and testing phases and was adapted from established reinforcement learning paradigms. Data were collected between 2019-2021 at the Cognitive Rhythms and Computation Lab at the University of New Mexico. This is the original raw dataset as published on OpenNeuro (ds004315).",
